Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @black sesame seeds{5%g} into another #bowl{}, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Dip the chicken first into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it is completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium-high heat. Add half the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Pour the @water{300%ml}(cold, for the rice) into the pan. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the saucepan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, heat a #small saucepan{} on medium heat (no oil). Add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @sambal paste{15%g} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Once thickened, remove from the heat.

> Careful, sambal paste is hot - add less if you don't like heat.

Meanwhile, pop a #large frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan. Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a clean plate lined with #kitchen paper{}. Clean out the #pan{} and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the remaining garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Allow to cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

When everything is ready, slice the chicken widthways. Share the rice between your #bowls{}, topped with the curry sauce (reheat first if needed), sliced chicken and a sprinkle of spring onion. Serve with the green beans alongside. Enjoy!